OL,3,CReligious hate crimes in England and
OL,4,CWales hit record high
OL,6,FThe Home Office said there was a
OL,7,F"clear spike in these offences in
OL,8,FAugust 2024, which coincides with the
OL,9,FSouthport murders on 29 July and the
OL,10,Fsubsequent disorder across several
OL,11,FEnglish towns and cities".
OL,13,FIn contrast, the figures revealed
OL,14,Freligious hate crimes targeted at
OL,15,FJewish people in the year ending March
OL,16,F2025 fell by 18% from 2,093 to 1,715,
OL,17,Fwhich the department cautioned does
OL,18,Fnot include Met Police data.
