OL,3,CReligious hate crimes in England and
OL,4,CWales hit record high
OL,6,FSeparately, the Met recorded that 40%
OL,7,Fof all religious hate crimes were
OL,8,Ftargeted at Jewish people in the last
OL,9,Fyear.
OL,11,FOverall police-recorded hate crimes in
OL,12,FEngland and Wales rose for the first
OL,13,Ftime in three years, while religiously
OL,14,Fmotivated offences reached a new
OL,15,Frecord.
OL,17,FPolice in England and Wales recorded
OL,18,F115,990 hate crimes in the year to
OL,19,FMarch, compared to 113,166 in the
OL,20,Fprevious year, which is up by 2%.
