OL,3,CReligious hate crimes in England and
OL,4,CWales hit record high
OL,6,FMeanwhile, hate crime offences
OL,7,Ftargeting sexual orientation,
OL,8,Fdisability and transgender, decreased
OL,9,Foverall.
OL,11,FThe figures show hate crimes based on
OL,12,Fsexual orientation fell by 2% to
OL,13,F19,127 from 18,702, and disability
OL,14,Fhate crimes dropped by 8% from 11,131
OL,15,Fto 10,224.
OL,17,FTransgender hate crimes fell by 11%
OL,18,Ffrom 4,258 to 3,809, the second
OL,19,Fconsecutive annual fall.
